defs.docs:
An experimental new error-handling library. Guide-style introduction
 is available [here](https://boats.gitlab.io/failure/).

defs.name: Backtrace
defs.docs: A `Backtrace`.

defs.name: new
defs.docs:
Constructs a new backtrace. This will only create a real backtrace
 if the crate is compiled in std mode and the `RUST_BACKTRACE`
 environmental variable is activated.

defs.name: is_empty
defs.docs: Returns true if displaying this backtrace would be an empty string.

defs.docs: A compatibility wrapper around an error type from this crate.

defs.docs: Unwraps this into the inner error.

defs.name: get_ref
defs.docs: Gets a reference to the inner error.

defs.name: Context
defs.docs: An error with context around it.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Creates a new context without an underlying error message.

defs.name: get_context
defs.docs: Returns a reference to the context provided with this error.

defs.name: map
defs.docs: Maps `Context<D>` to `Context<T>` by applying a function to the contained context.

defs.name: ResultExt
defs.docs: Extension methods for `Result`.

defs.name: compat
defs.docs:
Wraps the error in `Compat` to make it compatible with older error
 handling APIs that expect `std::error::Error`.

defs.name: context
defs.docs: Wraps the error type in a context type.

defs.name: with_context
defs.value: fn <F, D> (self, f: F) -> Result<T, Context<D>>
defs.docs:
Wraps the error type in a context type generated by looking at the
 error value.

defs.name: SyncFailure
defs.docs: Wrapper for `std` errors to make them `Sync`.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Wraps a non-`Sync` `Error` in order to make it implement `Fail`.

defs.name: Error
defs.docs: The `Error` type, which can contain any failure.

defs.name: from_boxed_compat
defs.value: fn (err: Box<dyn StdError + Sync + Send + 'static>) -> Error
defs.docs: Creates an `Error` from `Box<std::error::Error>`.

defs.name: as_fail
defs.docs:
Return a reference to the underlying failure that this `Error`
 contains.

defs.name: name
defs.docs: Returns the name of the underlying fail.

defs.name: cause
defs.docs:
Returns a reference to the underlying cause of this `Error`. Unlike the
 method on `Fail`, this does not return an `Option`. The `Error` type
 always has an underlying failure.

defs.name: backtrace
defs.docs: Gets a reference to the `Backtrace` for this `Error`.

defs.name: context
defs.docs: Provides context for this `Error`.

defs.name: compat
defs.docs: Wraps `Error` in a compatibility type.

defs.name: downcast
defs.docs: Attempts to downcast this `Error` to a particular `Fail` type.

defs.name: find_root_cause
defs.docs:
Returns the "root cause" of this error - the last value in the
 cause chain which does not return an underlying `cause`.

defs.name: iter_causes
defs.docs:
Returns a iterator over the causes of this error with the cause
 of the fail as the first item and the `root_cause` as the final item.

defs.name: iter_chain
defs.docs:
Returns a iterator over all fails up the chain from the current
 as the first item up to the `root_cause` as the final item.

defs.name: downcast_ref
defs.docs:
Attempts to downcast this `Error` to a particular `Fail` type by
 reference.

defs.name: downcast_mut
defs.docs:
Attempts to downcast this `Error` to a particular `Fail` type by
 mutable reference.

defs.name: Fail

defs.name: name
defs.docs:
Returns the "name" of the error.
 
 This is typically the type name. Not all errors will implement
 this. This method is expected to be most useful in situations
 where errors need to be reported to external instrumentation systems 
 such as crash reporters.

defs.name: cause
defs.docs:
Returns a reference to the underlying cause of this failure, if it
 is an error that wraps other errors.

defs.name: backtrace
defs.docs:
Returns a reference to the `Backtrace` carried by this failure, if it
 carries one.

defs.name: context
defs.docs: Provides context for this failure.

defs.name: compat
defs.docs:
Wraps this failure in a compatibility wrapper that implements
 `std::error::Error`.
